text: Xanlıqlar (known as Musaköy in the Soviet times and until 1994) is a village in the Qazakh Rayon of Azerbaijan. It has a population of 3,111. Xanliqlar is a place in Azerbaijan about 245 mi (or 395 km) west of Baku, the country's capital city. == References == * Category:Populated places in Qazakh District
title: Xanlıqlar, Qazakh
